<DOC><DOCNO> AP880617-0032 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-17-88 0254EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Pianist-Bunin     06-17 0109</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Pianist-Bunin,0115</SECOND><HEAD>Soviet Pianist Said To Apply For Asylum In West Germany</HEAD><DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A Soviet Embassy spokesman saidpianist Stanislaw Bunin has asked for political asylum in WestGermany.   However, West German officials said only that the Soviet pianisthad been granted an extension of his temporary residency permit.   ``We had a call from the (West German) Foreign Ministryinforming us that Bunin has applied for asylum here,'' SovietEmbassy spokesman Andre Serjogin said Thursday in Bonn.   But spokesmen for the West German Foreign and Interiorministries said they had no information about the matter.   Bunin came to West Germany on a concert tour.</TEXT></DOC>